description: From Middle English outaschouven, ut-ascufan, from Old English *ūtāscūfan, *ūtāscēofan (“to push out”), equivalent to out- +‎ shove.

verbs.description: outshove (third-person singular simple present outshoves, present participle outshoving, simple past and past participle outshoved)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To shove harder or better than; outcompete by shoving
